X3 Security Swarm Evidence Retention Policy

Every incident bundle must preserve watcher findings, judge assessments, warden votes, scribe output, runtime events, orchestrator events, related configuration versions, and any governance approvals that changed the incident outcome.

Evidence must be stored in immutable off-chain storage with an on-chain anchor for integrity verification. Raw logs may be tiered by sensitivity, but the final bundle hash, timeline, and sanction references must remain reproducible from retained artifacts.

The minimum retention period for finalized incident bundles is seven years. Drill reports and false-positive bundles may use a shorter local retention period, but their anchored hashes and summary metadata must remain queryable for audit continuity.
